Package org.aludratest.util.validator

Class Summary
AbstractNullStringValidator Parent class for AludraTest text validations: If the validation term is null, empty or equal to DataConfiguration.NULL_MARKER, it accepts any string.
AbstractNumberStringValidator Parent class for validators that check strings which contain numbers.
ContainsIgnoreCaseTrimmedValidator Requires strings to contain a sub string ignoring capitalization.
ContainsIgnoreCaseValidator Requires strings to contain an expected substring, ignoring capitalization.
ContainsValidator Expects the validated strings to contain the validation term.
EqualsIgnoreCaseTrimmedValidator Expects the validated strings to be equal to the search term ignoring case.
EqualsIgnoreCaseValidator Accepts strings that match the validation term ignoring capitalization.
EqualsValidator Expects strings to be identical to the validation term.
NotEqualsValidator Requires validated strings to be different from the validation term.
NumberStringGreaterValidator Requires numbers (formatted as strings) to be greater than a reference value.
NumberStringLessValidator Requires numbers (formatted as strings) to be less than a reference value.
